'''Refine '''items are used in the construction of more difficult to obtain items, requiring large amounts of a particular resource. For example, to gain anything that requires four [[Boards]], the player must collect 16 [[Log]]s. Eight items fall under the Refine category, or 13 in the ''[[Shipwrecked]]'' DLC. Refine Items are generally used in Tier Two recipes, such as the [[Alchemy Engine]]. [[Purple Gem]]s and [[Nightmare Fuel]] are often used in the [[Magic]] recipes, such as the [[Shadow Manipulator]]. The Refine tab is not automatically unlocked at the beginning of the game but is acquired through a [[Science Machine]].

==[[File:Gift Icon.png|32px]] Downloadable Content==
In the ''[[Shipwrecked]]'' DLC, the player can refine materials into [[Cloth]], [[Limestone]], [[Gold Nugget]]s, [[Coral Nubbin]]s, [[Ice]], and [[Empty Bottle]]s in the Refine Tab.

The ''[[Don't Starve: Hamlet|Hamlet]]'' DLC adds [[Claw Palm Sapling]]s and [[Venom Gland]]s to this tab. Additionally, it includes a different crafting recipe for Gold Nuggets.

